Consider the SIR model for COVID-19 in (1)–(3). Let Ω be the corona virus-load in an individual. Now, we consider the heterogeneity in the model by considering the power to infect in each individual as a function of the corona virus-load Ω. Therefore, the higher the corona virus-load in an individual, the higher the chance of the corona virus transmission in a contact interaction. By considering the corona virus-load Ω in each individual, the parameters β, \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
